  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6767 sitting right at the max negative gamma strike of 6765 (-41.1B), dealers are aggressively buying this dip as they're short gamma and forced to hedge dynamically. The massive negative GEX concentration between 6750-6770 creates a highly unstable zone where any move will be amplified by dealer flow, while the positive gamma wall at 6800 (+33.2B) acts as the key resistance where dealers will sell rallies. The recent GEX surge event combined with the breakout regime suggests we're in for violent two-way action until price either breaks decisively below 6750 (more dealer buying) or above 6800 (dealer selling kicks in).\n\n**Key levels:** 6750 breakdown triggers more dealer buying, 6800 breakthrough faces heavy dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect wild swings between 6750-6800 as dealers amplify every move.",
